      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VYTIS (6) made a nice return at his latest appearance a week ago, finishing third after racing parked at this venue. Up to a distance where he owns a good record and goes very well second-up with two wins and a placing from three attempts so can atone. MUSKEE (8) began badly last week but had been going very well prior, winning three of his previous four attempts. Can travel in a nice spot from this draw and wait on the sprint lane if necessary. Can bounce back. RINGER WELLS (3) progressed off a fresh placing to come from the back row and score by a head here last week. Plenty of room for further improvement so another win would not surprise. LITTLE YANKEE (5) returns to the front row and recorded a win and two placings from the last three times he started from there.",
